                <div class="jonra" data-uuid="fb618dad9edc4764aee550a5fb7c1c41">
                    <h2 data-uuid="2b67c7204ffc4ef3bdbd326199f4f061">The Vietnam Veterans Memorial</h2>
                    <p class="source" data-uuid="56baae56e92a41df8c17af23665048f7">Located on the National Mall, the Vietnam Veterans Memorial honors members of the U.S. armed forces who died in the Vietnam War, as well as those missing in action. Its main feature is a V-shaped wall inscribed with the names of more than 58,000 U.S. soldiers killed in the war. Initially, some thought the wall's simple design was not sufficiently respectful to the memory of fallen soldiers. Still, many
                        Vietnam veterans, their loved ones, and other visitors to the memorial have found the wall to be a deeply moving experience. Nearly every day, visitors leave offerings such as flowers, letters, dog tags, and photographs, at the memorial.</p>
                </div>
